President Biden has declared a major disaster in Montana due to flooding that occurred from June 1 to June 8, 2023. This declaration allows for federal assistance to supplement state, tribal, and local recovery efforts in the affected areas. Federal funding will be available for emergency work, repair or replacement of damaged facilities, and hazard mitigation measures. Alana B. Kuhn of FEMA has been appointed to coordinate federal recovery operations in the affected areas. Additional designations may be made in the future based on further damage assessments. For more information, the media can contact the FEMA News Desk.